Let me take you through a little #selfcareroutine with @wildsmithskin and their beautiful new gift sets which feature their super sustainable grown mycelium packaging.

The Cleansing duo is the epitome of #customisableskincare and a wonderful weekly exfoliation. The balm is beautiful and perfect for a little daily #selfcare

This £34 serum might just make you bin the cult classic.

Let’s Save Some Money — because your vitamin C serum shouldn’t cost more than your weekly food shop.

Everyone and their derm rates SkinCeuticals CE Ferulic — and yes, it’s iconic for a reason. But £165? That’s nearly five RoC serums and a Pret subscription.

Enter: @rocskincare.uk Revive and Glow Serum — £34 (full price but I may have found a bargain on my stories!). No, it doesn’t have ferulic acid, but it does have several antioxidants, peptides, and support proageing; think collagen production, elasticity, and anti-pigmentation. Basically, it delivers on glow without draining your bank account.

It’s not an exact dupe — but it’s a bloody good option if you’d like brighter skin and a working boiler.

Follow for more cheeky swaps, science-backed glow-ups, and skincare that won’t demand a kidney. 

#BeautyOnABudget #VitaminCDupe #SkinCeuticalsAlternative #SmartSkincare #Let’sSaveSomeMoney #RoCVitaminC #Over30SkinCare #MelaninSkinCare #GlowForLess #UKBeautyCommunity

*ROC serum previously received as part of an AD but this is not part of that campaign. I am under no obligation to post about it further. I just think it’s a bloody good alternative!

Just when I thought skincare couldn’t get any weirder… salmon sperm. Yes, really.

The buzz is all about PDRN (polydeoxyribonucleotide) — DNA fragments extracted from salmon sperm, long used in South Korean regenerative medicine, now popping up in serums and moisturisers promising firmer, glowier, more youthful skin.

The science? It’s said to boost skin repair, support collagen production, and help your skin bounce back faster — like a little cellular pep talk. Some call it “liquid Botox” (a phrase I personally find irritating as only botox is Botox)…Others call it… unsettling.

But it’s not for everyone — definitely skip if you’re vegan, allergic to fish, or your skin doesn’t like biologically active ingredients. And if your barrier isn’t in a good place, this isn’t where I’d start.

Worth it? Maybe — if you’ve nailed your basics: SPF, hydration, barrier care, and you’ve got budget to play with.

Would you try it? Or is fish jizz where you draw the skincare line?

Follow for honest takes, science-y skincare talk and the occasional ingredient drama.

📢 BREAKING: Rhode’s been snapped up by e.l.f., Medik8 just got bought by L’Oréal, and derm-loved Dr. Dennis Gross is now under Shiseido.

Is this the age of the beauty buyout?

I’ve just posted my first Substack breaking down what these acquisitions really mean for our skincare routines — the good, the bad, and the “please don’t reformulate my retinal serum.”

🧪 Big budgets mean innovation — but what about identity?
💄 Do influencer brands now have better business plans than heritage ones?
🇬🇧 And can a British brand like Medik8 survive going global?

Head to the link in bio to read the full post & let me know your take — is this a glow-up or a sellout?

#BeautyBusiness #SkincareNews #RhodeSkin #elfcosmetics #BeautyAcquisitions #SkincareCommunity #Skintellectuals #beautynews #BritishSkincare

A setting powder that feels like water? I didn’t believe it either.

But @makeuprevolution Hydra Cool Baking Powder is the weirdest—and most underrated—thing I’ve tried on my dehydrated under-eyes.

It’s lightweight, cooling, and somehow takes down shine without dulling your glow. No cakiness, no creasing, no “oh god what happened to my concealer by 2pm” moment.

And it’s currently £6. Six. Pounds. Which is wild considering how well it performs against some of the high-end powders gathering dust in my drawer.

If your skin’s dry, sensitive or over 30, this might just be your new go-to. Especially if you’re trying to set makeup without adding a decade.

💬 Have you tried a hydrating setting powder? Drop your recs—or your disasters—below. I’m building the dry-skin-girl-approved list.

This Week in Highlights: Hello Sunday, hydrated lips & a tee that made me snort.

Haircare:
Still loving the @colorwowhair One-Minute Transformation and Speed Dry spray. Genuinely no idea how they work but they make blow drying quicker and leave my hair very sleek. The @hairgainnow oScalp Foam is also staying in rotation—lightweight, doesn’t leave a trace, and the pro-hair growth tech is one I’ll be keeping an eye on.

Skincare:
Post-microneedling skin = sensitive. The @larocheposay Cicaplast Baume B5+ (with and without SPF) have proven to been brilliant as suspected. I’ve also brought the @e45_uk Hydrating Serum back into my morning routine—great under SPF, great hydration, affordable and helps keep skin calm.

Barrier Boosting Heroes:
The @nipandfab Ceramide Fix Balm Cleanser and Overnight Cream are still top of my list. Both have beautiful textures, and the cream has been a solid part of my night routine for months—deeply moisturising without leaving a film.

New In:
Had a great chat with the team at @hellosundayspf after their mineral SPF didn’t work for me—they sent over a few others to try and I really appreciate how receptive they were. Early signs are promising.

Also trying @theoutset Lip Oasis in ‘Dune’—demoed in stories last week. It’s hydrating, glossy and makes a great nude lip for low-effort days.

Fashion Picks:
Wearing the new limited edition vest from @brandedmoniker and had to pick up another personalised one (Guesses on the theme welcome, clue for those who’ve met me IRL…it’s on brand!) 

Also loving Pride Pilates socks from @moveactive are comfy, stay put during workouts, and just generally bring joy and externalise my allyship.

Out & About:
Back to @cultskin for another microneedling session with—more on that soon…

latestPosts.caption:
Turns out my real face still works — who knew?

I don’t use filters on this page. Partly for my own sanity, and partly because I’m raising a little human who’s already watching everything I do. If I want her to grow up comfortable in her own skin, I’ve got to be comfortable in mine — crow’s feet and all. 

And without clear filter banners, we know that the the filters and touch ups are being used on here by less than scrupulous influencers and brands who want to artificially enhance results you’re seeing. That can is open and the worms are everywhere. 

And look, I’m not here to judge the blur. I get it. Some days we all want to soften the edges. But the more we normalise real faces, the more space we make for everyone else to breathe too.

So here I am. Skin texture. Eye bags. No filter. Just me.

If you’ve been thinking about going filter-free — or you already have — I’d love to know how it’s felt for you. Confidence boost? Bit exposing? Somewhere in between? Let’s talk about it.

And @instagram @meta @mosseri please can we make it harder to filter without flags on here. The touch up button is quite frankly shameful in how covert it is. 

#FilterFreeFriday #NoFilterNeeded #HonestBeauty #SkinTextureIsNormal #RoleModelEnergy #UnfilteredAndFine #BeautyWithoutFilters #MumLifeUnfiltered #ThisIsThirtyPlus #RealTalkReels

Well… turns out I can’t count. But the glow is still glowing.

Let’s Save Some Money — because glowing skin is lovely, but so is paying your council tax on time.

This week’s match-up: @westmanatelier Vital Skin Drops vs @sculptedbyaimee Skin Tint.

Westman’s got the hype — sleek, bougie, and very spendy at £62. But if you’re after the same dewy, flexible coverage without the designer price tag, Sculpted by Aimee is absolutely, as the kids say, eating and leaving no crumbs. 

Hydrating, light-reflective, and blends like a dream — and all for under £25, because you could glow… or you could glow and buy lunch.

The maths may be off… but the swap still adds up.

Follow for more cheeky swaps, glow-ups, and beauty that doesn’t break the budget.

*previously AD| PR but since purchased. 

#BeautyOnABudget #SkinTintDupe #LetsSaveSomeMoney #SculptedByAimee #DewySkinForLess #SmartBeautyBuys #Over30Makeup #UKBeautyCommunity #MakeupThatGlows #BudgetMakeupFaves

Skin Transformation Journey

The real skin transformation? It started when I stopped fighting my face and started understanding it.

For years, I treated what I thought was acne—only to realise later it was rosacea. That one misdiagnosis kept me stuck in a cycle of over-treating, over-exfoliating, and wondering why nothing worked.

Once I understood my skin, with the help of insights from @dranitasturnham —what calmed it, what triggered it, what it was actually trying to tell me—everything changed. Not overnight. But slowly, gently, consistently.

And if something doesn’t feel right? Trust your gut. Your skin is always talking—you just have to get fluent in it.

This isn’t a perfect skin moment. It’s a healthy one.

If this serum ever gets discontinued, I will riot.

As a long-time fan of @sachiskin , the Pro Resilience Serum is the one I always come back to. It’s the skincare equivalent of a deep breath—reliable, restorative, and quietly powerful.

The INCI list reads like a who’s who of skin barrier support: Hydrators, pro-ageing Encapsulated Peptides, antioxidant Ayurvedic Bioflavonoid Complex, calming Glucosides, and barrier supportive skin identical lipid concentrate… basically, if it calms, protects or strengthens—it’s in there.

My skin loves this when it’s feeling reactive, hormonal, or just generally uncooperative. It’s helped keep my skin tone more even, my texture smoother, and my barrier intact—even during the rosacea wobbles.

If you’re new to the brand, this is the one I’d start with. And if you’re not… you already know.

💬 What’s your skin reset product? Always curious what others swear by.

Also bonus points if you can tell me in the comments, the not so deliberate continuity error, and the pitfalls of filming in London!

This Week in Highlights: SPF Experiments, Carbonara Cravings & a Cryo-Tipped Eye Cream

Skincare:
Trialling two new launches from @larocheposay —Anthelios UVair SPF 50+ (ultra-light, antioxidant-rich) and Cicaplast Baume B5+ SPF, which I’m hoping is post-microneedling-friendly. Updates to follow on the skin barrier saga. Also trialling @tropicskincare Eye Work serum; great inci and a cooling cryo tip that’s magic for puffiness. @alphahskincare  new enzyme exfoliator has dropped. Thoughts soon. 
 
Makeup:
It’s flushed skin season and I’m reaching for this combo:
– @merit Flush Balm in Lusitano
– @charlottetilbury Matte Revolution in 90s Pink
– @hudabeauty Faux Filler Gloss in Bombshell

Still using my go-to spray duo: CT to melt makeup between layers, Huda’s Easy Bake as a final mist for a powder-free set.

Lip Care:
Not cracked open the viral @olehenriksen Pout Preserve yet (viral videos made me want it), but loving @indewild peptide-packed Dewy Lip Treatment.

Bodycare:
Not glamorous, but @ineoshome Mandarin + Sandalwood deodorant has converted me. Smells like a unisex fragrance, keeps me dry all day.

New In:
@guvubeauty Eye Patches gave a real before/after lift. Also trying the @transformulas Marine Miracle duo—Giant Sea Kelp, Sea Salt and Centella Asiatica for firming and soothing.

Out & About:
Two top recs:
– The @londonphilharmonicorchestra family Petrushka show at @southbankcentre brilliant intro to classical music.
– Lunch at @circolopopolare.uk for the famous carbonara in a parmesan wheel. Over-the-top and very worth it.

Outfit:
Dress: @boden (past season)
Bag: @kurtgeiger (current + on sale)
Shoes: @adidasuk Spezial—my most-worn pair right now.

AD| Right, vitamin C fans—this one’s for you.

@officialmedik8 have just launched C-Tetra Advanced: a 20% vitamin C serum that’s all about brightening, hydrating and smoothing in one step. It’s gel-serum in texture (so lightweight, no stickiness) and clinically proven to visibly brighten skin in 7 days.

What’s inside:

– 20% THD Ascorbate: powerful, stabilised vitamin C that helps even tone and soften fine lines

– Acetyl Zingerone: a multitasking antioxidant that helps shield skin from pollution and boosts the brightening effect

– Phyto Exosomes: fancy plant messengers that support the skin barrier and deliver ingredients more effectively

– Hyaluronic Acid + 2% NAG: for hydration and smoother-looking pores

If your current vitamin C is more Cowper than Bridgerton, this might just be your season’s diamond.

Part of Medik8’s award-winning C-Tetra range—if you’re a fan already, this is the upgrade.
